00:00:00.740 --> 00:00:02.700
You've opened up a
shoe factory and you're

00:00:02.700 --> 00:00:06.020
trying to figure out how many
thousands of pairs of shoes

00:00:06.020 --> 00:00:08.980
to produce in order to
optimize your profit.

00:00:08.980 --> 00:00:13.505
And so let's let x equal the
thousands of pairs produced.

00:00:20.141 --> 00:00:21.640
Now let's think
about how much money

00:00:21.640 --> 00:00:22.990
you're going to make per pair.

00:00:22.990 --> 00:00:24.573
Actually, let me say
how much revenue,

00:00:24.573 --> 00:00:28.079
which is how much you actually
get to sell those shoes for.

00:00:28.079 --> 00:00:29.620
So let's write a
function right here.

00:00:29.620 --> 00:00:31.910
Revenue as a function of x.

00:00:31.910 --> 00:00:33.470
Well, you have a
wholesaler who's

00:00:33.470 --> 00:00:36.720
willing to pay you $10
per pair for as many pairs

00:00:36.720 --> 00:00:38.090
as you're willing to give him.

00:00:38.090 --> 00:00:42.100
So your revenue as a function
of x is going to be 10 times x.

00:00:42.100 --> 00:00:45.490
And since x is in thousands
of pairs produced, if x is 1,

00:00:45.490 --> 00:00:50.500
that means 1,000 pairs produced
times 10, which means $10,000.

00:00:50.500 --> 00:00:51.980
But this will just give you 10.

00:00:51.980 --> 00:00:54.350
So this right over here is
in thousands of dollars.

00:01:00.060 --> 00:01:02.570
So if x is 1, that means
1,000 pairs produced.

00:01:02.570 --> 00:01:05.260
10 times 1 says
r is equal to 10,

00:01:05.260 --> 00:01:09.689
but that really means $10,000.

00:01:09.689 --> 00:01:11.480
Now, it would be a nice
business if all you

00:01:11.480 --> 00:01:13.210
had was revenue and no costs.

00:01:13.210 --> 00:01:14.465
But you do have costs.

00:01:14.465 --> 00:01:16.590
You have materials, you
have to build your factory,

00:01:16.590 --> 00:01:18.089
have to pay your
employees, you have

00:01:18.089 --> 00:01:19.500
to pay the electricity bill.

00:01:19.500 --> 00:01:21.210
And so you hire a
bunch of consultants

00:01:21.210 --> 00:01:24.945
to come up with what your
cost is as a function of x.

00:01:28.170 --> 00:01:29.600
And they come up
with a function.

00:01:29.600 --> 00:01:33.270
They say it is the number of the
thousands of pairs you produce

00:01:33.270 --> 00:01:36.920
cubed minus 6 times the
thousands of pairs you produce

00:01:36.920 --> 00:01:41.950
squared plus 15 times
the thousands of pairs

00:01:41.950 --> 00:01:43.300
that you produce.

00:01:43.300 --> 00:01:46.580
And once again,
this is also going

00:01:46.580 --> 00:01:49.710
to be in thousands of dollars.

00:01:49.710 --> 00:01:54.682
Now, given these functions
of x for revenue and cost,

00:01:54.682 --> 00:01:58.930
what is profit as a
function of x going to be?

00:01:58.930 --> 00:02:03.580
Well, your profit
as a function of x

00:02:03.580 --> 00:02:07.710
is just going to be equal to
your revenue as a function of x

00:02:07.710 --> 00:02:09.800
minus your cost as
a function of x.

00:02:12.592 --> 00:02:14.300
If you produce a
certain amount and let's

00:02:14.300 --> 00:02:17.330
say you bring in, I don't
know, $10,000 of revenue

00:02:17.330 --> 00:02:19.970
and it costs you $5,000
to produce those shoes,

00:02:19.970 --> 00:02:21.529
you'll have $5,000 in profit.

00:02:21.529 --> 00:02:23.570
Those numbers aren't the
ones that would actually

00:02:23.570 --> 00:02:25.250
you would get from
this right here.

00:02:25.250 --> 00:02:27.230
I'm just giving you an example.

00:02:27.230 --> 00:02:28.990
So this is what you
want to optimize.

00:02:28.990 --> 00:02:36.170
You want to optimize
p as a function of x.

00:02:36.170 --> 00:02:37.140
So what is it?

00:02:37.140 --> 00:02:39.070
I've just said it here
in abstract terms,

00:02:39.070 --> 00:02:41.170
but we know what r of
x is and what's c of x.

00:02:41.170 --> 00:02:46.380
This is 10x minus
all of this business.

00:02:46.380 --> 00:02:53.590
So minus x to the third
plus 6x squared minus 15x.

00:02:53.590 --> 00:02:56.110
I just subtracted x
squared, you subtract

00:02:56.110 --> 00:02:58.880
6x squared it becomes positive,
you subtract a 15x it becomes

00:02:58.880 --> 00:03:03.520
negative 15x, and then we can
simplify this as-- let's see,

00:03:03.520 --> 00:03:07.200
we have negative x
to the third plus 6x

00:03:07.200 --> 00:03:12.370
squared minus 15x plus
10x, so that is minus 5x.

00:03:12.370 --> 00:03:16.497
Now if we want to optimize this
profit function analytically,

00:03:16.497 --> 00:03:18.080
the easiest way is
to think about what

00:03:18.080 --> 00:03:20.240
are the critical points
of this profit function

00:03:20.240 --> 00:03:21.740
and are any of those
critical points

00:03:21.740 --> 00:03:23.430
minimum points or
maximum points?

00:03:23.430 --> 00:03:26.870
And if one of them is a
maximum point, then we can say,

00:03:26.870 --> 00:03:28.190
well, let's produce that many.

00:03:28.190 --> 00:03:30.292
That is going to be--
we will have optimized

00:03:30.292 --> 00:03:32.500
or we will figure out the
quantity we need to produce

00:03:32.500 --> 00:03:35.020
in order to optimize our profit.

00:03:35.020 --> 00:03:36.710
So to figure out
critical points,

00:03:36.710 --> 00:03:39.600
we essentially have to find
the derivative of our function

00:03:39.600 --> 00:03:42.110
and figure out when does
that derivative equal 0

00:03:42.110 --> 00:03:44.070
or when is that
derivative undefined?

00:03:44.070 --> 00:03:46.490
That's the definition
of critical points.

00:03:46.490 --> 00:03:50.960
So p prime of x is going
to be equal to negative 3x

00:03:50.960 --> 00:03:55.790
squared plus 12x minus 5.

00:03:55.790 --> 00:03:58.100
And so this thing is going
to be defined for all x.

00:03:58.100 --> 00:04:00.140
So the only critical
points we're going to have

00:04:00.140 --> 00:04:04.280
is when the first derivative
right over here is equal to 0.

00:04:04.280 --> 00:04:10.470
So negative 3x squared plus 12x
minus 5 needs to be equal to 0

00:04:10.470 --> 00:04:12.190
in order for x to
be a critical point.

00:04:12.190 --> 00:04:14.300
So now we just have
to solve for x.

00:04:14.300 --> 00:04:17.829
And so we just are essentially
solving a quadratic equation.

00:04:17.829 --> 00:04:19.860
Just so that I don't
have as many negatives,

00:04:19.860 --> 00:04:21.820
let's multiply both
sides by negative 1.

00:04:21.820 --> 00:04:24.040
I just like to have a
clean first coefficient.

00:04:24.040 --> 00:04:25.950
So if we multiply both
sides by negative 1,

00:04:25.950 --> 00:04:33.330
we get 3x squared minus
12x plus 5 is equal to 0.

00:04:33.330 --> 00:04:36.700
And now we can use the quadratic
formula to solve for x.

00:04:36.700 --> 00:04:41.960
So x is going to be equal
to negative b, which is 12,

00:04:41.960 --> 00:04:43.910
plus or minus the square root.

00:04:43.910 --> 00:04:46.650
I always need to make my
radical signs wide enough.

00:04:46.650 --> 00:04:48.840
The square root of
b squared, which

00:04:48.840 --> 00:04:56.340
is 144, minus 4 times a, which
is 3, times c, which is 5.

00:04:59.340 --> 00:05:01.020
All of that over 2a.

